sec.p:
None of the cadets engaged in organised competitive sport during the semester before enrolment; all conditioning derived from the Academy’s compulsory programme (three 90 min callisthenics/endurance sessions plus one 10 km loaded run weekly). MET values for each field-exercise task were estimated from the 2022 Compendium of Physical Activities and cross-checked against mean heart rate (%HRmax) and session-RPE recordings. Marching with 20–25 kg at 4–5 km h−¹ corresponded to 6.0–7.5 METs, obstacle-course work to 8–10 METs, and live-fire marksmanship to 4 METs. Daily, weighted averages were as follows:
Day 1–2 5.0 ± 0.9 METs (moderate, 3–6 METs);
Day 3–5 8.3 ± 1.1 METs (vigorous, >6 METs);
Day 6–10 5.4 ± 1.0 METs (upper-moderate).

